data.content:
## .NET 10 OpenAPI Breaking Changes

The root cause is that `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` 10.0 upgraded from **Microsoft.OpenApi v1** to **v2**, which targets **OpenAPI 3.1** and has significant API changes.

Here's each issue and its fix:

### 1. `OpenApiString` / `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` types removed
The `IOpenApiAny` hierarchy is gone. Use `System.Text.Json.Nodes.JsonNode` instead:

```csharp
// OLD
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// NEW
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

### 2. `Schema.Nullable` removed
OpenAPI 3.1 uses a type array instead of a `nullable` flag. The `Type` property is now a `JsonSchemaType` flags enum:

```csharp
// OLD
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// NEW — remove the Null flag from the type
property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;

// To make nullable, you would do:
// property.Value.Type |= JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

### 3. `OpenApiSecurityRequirement` is no longer a dictionary
It no longer inherits from `Dictionary<OpenApiSecurityScheme, IList<string>>`. Use the `Schemes` property instead:

```csharp
// OLD
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
};

// NEW
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new()
    {
        Schemes = new Dictionary<OpenApiSecurityScheme, IList<string>>
        {
            [oAuthScheme] = scopes
        }
    }
};
```

### Full fixed code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
    {
        Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
    };
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new()
        {
            Schemes = new Dictionary<OpenApiSecurityScheme, IList<string>>
            {
                [oAuthScheme] = scopes
            }
        }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

### Summary of changes

| .NET 9 (OpenApi v1) | .NET 10 (OpenApi v2) |
|---|---|
| `new OpenApiString("x")` | `JsonValue.Create("x")` |
| `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` | `using System.Text.Json.Nodes` |
| `schema.Nullable = bool` | `schema.Type \|= / &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null` |
| `new() { [scheme] = scopes }` | `new() { Schemes = new Dictionary<…> { … } }` |
